<DOCUMENT source-infobase-name="Admin" content-collection-id="NYCadmin" source-infobase-title="New York City Administrative Code" base-output-dir="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCadmin\output\QYOUGRVBABWOEQAB\" default-split-level="Chapter" makefile-filename="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCadmin\output\QYOUGRVBABWOEQAB\NYCadmin.mak" css-stylesheet-href="#!-- #ID=NYCadmin_css_id --#" xml-output-dir="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCadmin\output\QYOUGRVBABWOEQAB\XML\" css-stylesheet-name="NYCadmin_css" makefile-document-depth="2">
	<LEVEL style-name="Chapter" style-name-escaped="Chapter" style-id="0-0-0-685" level-depth="2" toc-section="false">
		<RECORD id="0-0-0-112723" number="49928" version="134">
			<HEADING>Chapter 27: After School Athletic Funding</HEADING>
			<PARA>
				<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-19223" name="T21-aC027"/>Chapter 27: After School Athletic Funding</PARA>
		</RECORD>
		<LEVEL style-name="Subchapter" style-name-escaped="Subchapter" style-id="0-0-0-688" level-depth="3" toc-section="false">
			<LEVEL style-name="Appendix" style-name-escaped="Appendix" style-id="0-0-0-691" level-depth="4" toc-section="false">
				<LEVEL style-name="Part" style-name-escaped="Part" style-id="0-0-0-694" level-depth="5" toc-section="false">
					<LEVEL style-name="Article" style-name-escaped="Article" style-id="0-0-0-697" level-depth="6" toc-section="false">
						<LEVEL style-name="Subarticle" style-name-escaped="Subarticle" style-id="0-0-0-700" level-depth="7" toc-section="false">
							<LEVEL style-name="Subarticle - Part" style-name-escaped="Subarticle---Part" style-id="0-0-0-29474" level-depth="8" toc-section="false">
								<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-703" level-depth="9" toc-section="true">
									<RECORD id="0-0-0-112724" number="49929" version="134">
										<HEADING>§ 21-998 After school athletic funding.</HEADING>
										<PARA>
											<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-19225" name="21-998"/>§ 21-998 After school athletic funding.</PARA>
									</RECORD>
									<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-112745" number="49930" version="134">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>a.<TAB tab-count="1"/>For the purposes of this section, the following terms have the following meanings: <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-038]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-112744" number="49931" version="1765">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Athletic facility.</CHARFORMAT> The term &quot;athletic facility&quot; means an indoor or outdoor facility used by high schools for athletics. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-038]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-112743" number="49932" version="1765">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Athletics.</CHARFORMAT> The term &quot;athletics&quot; means after school interscholastic athletic competition for students. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-038]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-112742" number="49933" version="1765">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">High school.</CHARFORMAT> The term &quot;high school&quot; means a school of the city school district of the city of New York that contains any combination of grades from and including grade nine through grade 12. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-038]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-112741" number="49934" version="1765">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Student.</CHARFORMAT> The term &quot;student&quot; means any pupil under the age of 21 as of September first of the academic period being reported, who does not have a high school diploma and who is enrolled in a high school. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-038]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-112740" number="49935" version="1762">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>b.<TAB tab-count="1"/>No later than December 1, 2019, and annually thereafter, the department shall submit to the speaker of the council and post on the department&apos;s website an athletics report for the preceding academic year, which shall include, but not be limited to, the following: <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-038]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-112739" number="49936" version="134">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>1.<TAB tab-count="1"/>For each high school, the total amount of funding provided by the department for athletics and the amount of such funding allocated for each of the following categories: (i) coaches and athletic directors, and (ii) other than personal service related to the public schools athletic league; <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-038]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-112738" number="49937" version="134">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>2.<TAB tab-count="1"/>For each high school, the total number of students participating in athletics and the number and percentage of such students disaggregated by: <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-038]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-112737" number="49938" version="134">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>(a)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Race or ethnicity; <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-038]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-112736" number="49939" version="134">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>(b)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Gender; <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-038]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-112735" number="49940" version="134">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>(c)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Special education status; <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-038]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-112734" number="49941" version="134">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>(d)<TAB tab-count="1"/>English language learner status; and <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-038]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-112733" number="49942" version="134">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>(e)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Calendar year of entry to grade nine; <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-038]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-112732" number="49943" version="134">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>3.<TAB tab-count="1"/>A list of all criteria used by the department when making decisions about new team requests including any changes in the criteria from the preceding academic year; <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-038]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-112731" number="49944" version="134">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>4.<TAB tab-count="1"/>A list of all new team requests received by the department, including the high school that submitted such request, whether each request was approved or denied by the department and the reason for such approval or denial; and <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-038]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-112730" number="49945" version="134">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>5.<TAB tab-count="1"/>A list of all athletic facilities used by high schools in the prior academic year, including athletic facilities under the jurisdiction of the department of parks and recreation. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-038]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-112729" number="49946" version="134">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>c.<TAB tab-count="1"/>The report required pursuant to this section shall provide citywide data, as well as data disaggregated by borough and community school district, except that paragraph 5 of subdivision b of this section shall be disaggregated solely by borough. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-038]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-112728" number="49947" version="134">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>d.<TAB tab-count="1"/>No information that is otherwise required to be reported pursuant to this section shall be reported in a manner that would violate any applicable provision of federal, state, or local law relating to the privacy of student information or that would interfere with law enforcement investigations or otherwise conflict with the interest of law enforcement. If a category contains between one and five students, or allows another category to be narrowed to between one and five students, the number shall be replaced with a symbol. A category that contains zero shall be reported as zero, unless such reporting would violate any applicable provision of federal, state or local law relating to the privacy of student information. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-038]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-112726" number="49948" version="709">
											<PARA>(L.L. 2019/120, 6/29/2019, eff. 6/29/2019) <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-038]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-112725" number="49949" version="491">
											<PARA style-name="EdNoteSm" style-name-escaped="EdNoteSm" style-id="0-0-0-18">
												<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Editor&apos;s note:</CHARFORMAT> For related unconsolidated provisions, see Appendix A at <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-23" type="Jump" destination-name="L.L. 2019/120" destination-id="0-0-0-20371">L.L. 2019/120</LINK>. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-053]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
									</LEVEL>
								</LEVEL>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
					</LEVEL>
				</LEVEL>
			</LEVEL>
		</LEVEL>
	</LEVEL>
